description:
On this episode of ANN International: Local San Bernardino diaper distribution program celebrates reaching its milestone of giving out one million diapers.

The Prince of Eswatini, a Southern African country bordering Mozambique and South Africa, accepts baptism, joined by others from the royal guard.

Also, Japan officially opens the doors to its first Adventist Center of Influence.

Stay tuned as ANN brings you these captivating stories and provides coverage of other global news. For a deeper dive into these headlines and more, visit adventist.news.

ANN is the official news channel of the Seventh-day Adventist Church.
